    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="880"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In the event of hostilities between United States and Spain, the policy of this
                    Government will be not to resort to privateering, but to adhere to the following
                    recognized rules of international law: First, the neutral flag covers enemy’s
                    goods, with the exception of contraband of war; second, neutral goods, with the
                    exception of contraband of war, are not liable to capture under the enemy’s
                    flag; and, third, blockades in order to be binding must be effective.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
